<HEADLINE>
<P>
COST OF U.S. INTERVENTION IN THE MIDEAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We were quick to do everything to mobilize the military to defend Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
We were quick to do nothing to defend those the soldiers left at home from 
price gouging. 
</P>
<P>
We were quick to do nothing to defend working mothers who need leave time to 
bear America's newborn babes -- our future soldiers. In fact the Administration 
mobilized its forces and vetoed the legislation granting such leave. 
</P>
<P>
ALBERT NASSER 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
</TEXT>
