<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: NATIONAL TECHNICAL POSTS 7% DROP IN 2ND QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Technical Systems Inc., a Calabasas provider of testing and 
engineering services, said its fiscal second-quarter profit fell 7% from a year 
earlier as revenue remained flat. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter ended July 31, National Technical's net income dropped to 
$212,000 from $228,000, and its revenue was unchanged at $7.63 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of its fiscal year, the company's profit fell 20% from a 
year earlier, to $413,000 from $513,000, and its six-month revenue also was 
unchanged at $15.4 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
