<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: MOORPARK; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL TO DISCUSS HIGH SCHOOL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A special Moorpark City Council committee meeting to discuss buying the Casey 
Road site where Moorpark Memorial High School sits will be held Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The committee will meet with the Moorpark Unified School District board to 
consider the sale, which has been the source of a legal battle between the city 
and the school district for more than two years. 
</P>
<P>
The school district wants to sell the property for development, but the city 
ruled that development would increase traffic in the downtown area. The city 
wants to buy part of the property at a reduced price to build a city park. 
</P>
<P>
The site is now used for a continuation high school. 
</P>
<P>
The public meeting will begin at 4:30 p.m. in the board room of the Moorpark 
Unified School District. LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</TEXT>
