<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A shotgun-wielding bandit fled with up to $20,000 after robbing a Linda Vista 
Road food market, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A man wearing a knit mask entered Victory Foods, 6935 Linda Vista Road, shortly 
after 6 a.m. Sunday and fired a blast from his shotgun into a wastebasket 
before ordering the store's employees into a back room, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The employees said the man took $15,000 to $20,000 and fled on foot, according 
to police. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported and no more information was available. 
</P>
