<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were robbed within minutes of each other early Monday, and police 
believe that the same man armed with a 9-millimeter semiautomatic pistol may 
have been involved in both crimes. 
</P>
<P>
The first victim told Escondido police that he had gotten out of his car in the 
2300 block of Escondido Boulevard to shop in an all-night mini-market when a 
stocky gunman robbed him of $30. 
</P>
<P>
A few minutes later another man was stopped by two men in the 2800 block of 
Verda Avenue near the first holdup as he got out of his parked car. The robbers 
demanded money as one held a gun on the victim. He struggled with one of the 
robbers, but his wallet and keys were taken. 
</P>
<P>
In both incidents the suspects drove away in a lowered minivan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
