<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOM MARTIN PROVIDES INTERESTING OPENING ACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GLENN DOGGRELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opening the show for Paul Rodriguez was Tom Martin, an Orange County comic with 
a soft style and easy flow. 
</P>
<P>
Here are some examples of why he is worth catching: 
</P>
<P>
He is out to dinner with his family and orders a grilled cheese sandwich, only 
to be admonished by his mother and told to get something he can't get at home. 
In that case, "I'll have some understanding and compassion, please." 
</P>
<P>
Talking about how messy he and his college roommate were, he says: "The 
landlord asked us to wipe our feet before going outside." GLENN DOGGRELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Sidebar; Concert Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
