<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kristina Lindgren and Tony Marcano 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UP AND UP: Community college enrollment (above) has been climbing steadily in 
Orange County since it bottomed out in 1985, the year tuition was introduced. . 
. . Now, with the talk of recession, administrators are expecting even greater 
gains. "Historically, when employment gets tight, people go back to school," 
says one administrator. . . . Has it begun already? Opening-day enrollment at 
Orange Coast College, the county's biggest, was up 15%, but officials say they 
are unsure of the reason. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
