<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
INDIA; 
</P>
<P>
MUSLIM MILITANTS ATTACK IN KASHMIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Militants firing rockets, grenades and machine guns attacked security patrols 
in the Kashmiri summer capital of Srinagar. The state government in 
Indian-ruled Kashmir virtually collapsed as about 135,000 public employees 
began a weeklong strike to protest the alleged brutality of Indian security 
police. At least nine people were killed in clashes between protesters and the 
security forces in the Kashmir Valley, where Muslim militants are campaigning 
for independence or merger with Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
