</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SOMALIA; 
</P>
<P>
GOVERNMENT SACKED AFTER SIX MONTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Mohamed Siad Barre sacked the 6-month-old government of Prime 
Minister Mohamed Ali Samantar. 
</P>
<P>
Barre gave no reason for the move in Mogadishu, but the East African nation has 
been convulsed by rebellions and banditry. Mohamed Hawadle Madar, an ex-Cabinet 
minister, was asked to form a new government. He is a member of the Isaak clan, 
a major supporter of the rebel Somali National Movement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
