TOXIC CLOUD FROM FIRE FORCES 800 TO EVACUATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A toxic cloud from a fire in a La Verne computer parts manufacturing company 
forced the evacuation of about 800 residents Sunday night and sent eight 
individuals, including three firefighters and two police officers to the 
hospital, officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Many of those evacuated, including residents of nearby mobile home parks, were 
out of their homes for nearly 24 hours before officials declared the area safe 
about 4 p.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was discovered about 8:30 p.m. Sunday at the Super Tech plant at 1st 
and E streets, fire officials said. The eight injured, including two residents, 
experienced "major" headaches, nausea and blurred vision, said La Verne Police 
Lt. Jim Crawford, who ordered the evacuation. All were treated at Pomona Valley 
Hospital and released. 
</P>
