<P>
SOUTER WINS HIGHEST BAR RATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Supreme Court nominee David H. Souter today received the highest rating from 
the American Bar Assn.'s judicial screening panel, the Justice Department said. 
</P>
<P>
Souter received a unanimous "well-qualified" rating from the ABA's Standing 
Committee on Federal Judiciary, according to a letter from the panel to the 
Justice Department. 
</P>
<P>
Souter, a former member of the New Hampshire Supreme Court, was nominated by 
President Bush in July for the vacancy created by the retirement of Associate 
Justice William J. Brennan Jr. 
</P>
<P>
Souter received a similar "well-qualified" rating earlier this year when he was 
nominated for a seat on the U.S. 1st Circuit Court of Appeals in Boston. 
</P>
