<P>
2 ESCAPE JAIL HOLDING NORIEGA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MIAMI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two inmates at the prison where Manuel A. Noriega is being held dodged bullets 
while scaling a fence and escaped in a sports car apparently left for them with 
the keys inside, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The ousted Panamanian dictator, under constant watch by a guard posted outside 
his specially built cell at the federal Metropolitan Correctional Center, was 
not involved. 
</P>
<P>
Omar Fernandez of Miami and Charles Carew of Brockton, Mass., were spotted 
climbing a fence Monday night, said prison spokesman Charles Davis. 
</P>
<P>
Fernandez, 24, and Carew, 28, were caught separately about an hour before dawn 
and within about a mile of the prison, prison Lt. Thoman Litwinski said. No 
further details were given. 
</P>
</TEXT>
