<P>
CONSTRUCTION POSTS SLIGHT RISE IN JULY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction spending posted a slight 0.4% gain in July, the first advance in 
four months, the government reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department said residential, non-residential and government 
spending totaled a seasonally adjusted annual rate of $442.2 billion. 
</P>
<P>
Construction spending had not risen since a 0.4% increase in March. It had 
fallen 0.9% in both May and June and 1.9% in April. 
</P>
