<P>
WYNETTE PICKS A LIVELY MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EVELETH, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Country music singer Tammy Wynette just happened to spend the night in a motel 
where police had a standoff with an armed man who barricaded himself in his 
room for more than five hours. 
</P>
<P>
Customers in nearby rooms were evacuated and there were no injuries, Police 
Chief James Bozicevich said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who was alone in the room, surrendered after authorities broke a 
window early Monday and tossed in two tear gas canisters, Bozicevich said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither Wynette nor any member of her crew was associated with the man or the 
incident, Bozicevich said. The chief said Wynette was staying in a part of the 
motel that was not evacuated. She was in the Iron Range area of northern 
Minnesota to perform at Ironworld USA in nearby Chisholm. 
</P>
<P>
The chief said someone reported late Sunday that the man had pointed a gun at 
someone. No shots were fired, the chief said. 
</P>
<P>
The man from Mayfield, Ky., had more than one gun in his possession when he 
surrendered, he said. 
</P>
