<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN WAYNE AIRPORT; 
</P>
<P>
TRAVEL TIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Preparing for your flight as you would an important meeting can help you get a 
grip on your worst fears." 
</P>
<P>
Jeffrey Kasdorf, PhobiaCare Treatment Center. 
</P>
<P>
"One blouse works with two or three outfits. resist the temptation to throw in 
something at the last minute." 
</P>
<P>
Kitty Leslie, Fashion Director. 
</P>
<P>
"When using the airport, be aware of what's going on around you. The most 
common crimes are 'distraction thefts.' ". 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Ken Lohrey, Sheriff Department's Airport Bureau. 
</P>
<P>
"To reduce that sluggish feeling you can do stretching exercise in your 
airplane seat that won't bother your neighbors." 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Geoffrey Ricchio, Chiropractic Rehabilitation Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
